8/http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/soccer/world/events/1998/worldcup/teams/jamaica/player_profiles.html|archive-date=14 May 2004|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Player records==\n===Most capped players===\nThe top 10 most capped players - players with an equal number of [[cap (sport)|cap]]s are ranked in chronological order of reaching the milestone.<ref name=\"rsssf jamaica players\">{{cite web |url=http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/jam-recintlp.html |title=Jamaica&nbsp;\u2013 Record International Players |author=Mamrud, Roberto |publisher=RSSSF |accessdate=18 November 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190321143616/http://www.rsssf.com/miscellaneous/jam-recintlp.html |archive-date=21 March 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!width=50px|#\n! style=\"width:150px;\"|Player\n!width=50px|Caps\n!width=50px|Goals\n! style=\"width:100px;\"|Career\n|-\n| 1 || [[Ian Goodison]] || 128 || 10 || 1996\u20132009\n|-\n| 2 || [[Linval Dixon]] || 127 || 3 || 1993\u20132003\n|-\n| 3 || [[Theodore Whitmore]] || 120 || 24 || 1993\u20132004\n|-\n| 4 || [[Ricardo Gardner]] || 111 || 9 || 1997\u20132012\n|-\n| 5 || [[Warren Barrett]] || 108 || 0 || 1990\u20132000\n|-\n| 6 || [[Andy Williams (Jamaican footballer)|Andy Williams]] || 107 || 22 || 1997\u20132008\n|-\n| 7 || [[Durrant Brown]] || 102 || 0 || 1984\u20131998\n|-\n| 8 || [[Donovan Ricketts]] || 100 || 0 || 1999\u20132013\n|-\n| 9 || [[Jermaine Taylor (footballer)|Jermaine Taylor]] || 99 || 0 || 2004\u20132017\n|-\n| 10 || [[Rodolph Austin]] || 88 || 7 || 2004\u20132016\n|}\n\n===Top goalscorers===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n|+Top Goalscorers\n|-\n!width=50px|#\n! style=\"width:150px;\"|Player\n!width=50px|Goals\n!width=50px|Caps\n! style=\"width:100px;\"|Career\n|-\n| 1 || [[Luton Shelton]] || 35 || 75 || 2004\u20132013\n|-\n| 2 || [[Onandi Lowe]] || 27 || 81 || 1995\u20132004\n|-\n| 3 || [[Theodore Whitmore]] || 24 || 120 || 1993\u20132004\n|-\n| 4 || [[Andy Williams (Jamaican footballer)|Andy Williams]] || 22 || 97 || 1997\u20132008\n|-\n| = || [[Paul Young (footballer, born 1968)|Paul Young]] || 22 || 49 || 1989\u20131997\n|-\n| 6 || [[Walter Boyd (footballer)|Walter Boyd]] || 19 || 75 || 1991\u20132001\n|-\n| 7 || [[Paul Davis (footballer, born 1962)|Paul Davis]] || 18 || 61 || 1983\u20131997\n|-\n| 8 || '''[[Darren Mattocks]]''' || 18 || 44 || 2012\u2013\n|-\n| 9 || [[Hector Wright]] || 16 || 71 || 1988\u20131997\n|-\n| 10 || [[Paul Hall (footballer)|Paul Hall]] || 14 || 48 || 1997\u20132003\n|}\n{{updated|November 17, 2018}}\n\n==Competitive record==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:30%; font-size:90%; text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!style=\"color:yellow; background:black;\" colspan=\"5\" | Overview\n|-\n! Event\n!style=\"width:14%; background:gold;\" | 1st place\n!style=\"width:14%; background:silver;\" | 2nd place\n!style=\"width:14%; background:#c96;\" | 3rd place\n!style=\"width:14%; background:LemonChiffon;\" | 4th place\n|-\n|align=left|[[FIFA World Cup|World Cup]]\n! 0\n! 0\n! 0\n! 0 \n|-\n|align=left|{{nowrap|[[CONCACAF Gold Cup|Gold Cup]]}}\n! 0\n! 2\n! 1\n! 2\n|-\n|align=left|[[Caribbean Cup]]\n! 6\n! 3\n! 2\n! 0\n|-\n|align=left|[[Copa Am\u00e9rica]]\n! 0\n! 0\n! 0\n! 0\n|}\n\n===FIFA World Cup===\n{{main|Jamaica at the FIFA World Cup}}\nJamaica's only appearance at the FIFA World Cup was in 1998. The team opened with a 3\u20131 loss against [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]] in Lens. After falling behind in the 27th minute, [[Robbie Earle]] scored the equalizer to close the first half. In the second half, Croatia scored two goals, causing Jamaica to lose the match.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.chicagotribune.com/news/ct-xpm-1998-06-15-9806150083-story.html|title=Croatia 3, Jamaica 1|first=Bonnie|last=DeSimone|location=Lens|publisher=Chicago Tribute|date=15 June 1998|access-date=13 June 2019}}</ref> The second match against [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]] saw [[Gabriel Batistuta]] getting a second half hat-trick, aiding in Jamaica's second defeat and elimination from the World Cup.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thefreelibrary.com/Hat-trick+helps+finish+the+Reggae+Boyz%3b+ARGENTINA+5+JAMAICA+0.-a060783024|title=Hat-trick helps finish the Reggae Boyz; Argentina 5 Jamaica 0.|publisher=Birmingham Post|date=22 June 1998|access-date=13 June 2019}}</ref> In the final match of the tournament, Theodore Whitmore scored a double, securing Jamaica's first World Cup win with a 2\u20131 win over Japan.<ref name=JapanvsJamaica1998/>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n! style=\"color:yellow; background:black;\" colspan=10|[[FIFA World Cup|{{yellow|FIFA World Cup}}]] record\n! style=\"width:1%;background:white\" rowspan=\"26\"|\n! style=\"color:yellow; background:black;\" colspan=7|[[FIFA World Cup qualification|{{yellow|Qualification}}]] record\n|-\n!Year\n!Round\n!Position\n!{{Tooltip|Pld|Games played}}\n!{{Tooltip|W|Won}}\n!{{Tooltip|D|Drawn}}\n!{{Tooltip|L|Lost}}\n!{{Tooltip|GF|Goals for}}\n!{{Tooltip|GA|Goals against}}\n!Squads\n!{{Tooltip|Pld|Games played}}\n!{{Tooltip|W|Won}}\n!{{Tooltip|D|Drawn}}\n!{{Tooltip|L|Lost}}\n!{{Tooltip|GF|Goals for}}\n!{{Tooltip|GA|Goals against}}\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Uruguay}} [[1930 FIFA World Cup|1930]]\n|colspan=9 rowspan=7|''Did not enter''\n|colspan=6 rowspan=7|''Declined participation''\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Italy|1861}} [[1934 FIFA World Cup|1934]]\n|-\n|{{flagicon|France|1794}} [[1938 FIFA World Cup|1938]]\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Brazil|1889}} [[1950 FIFA World Cup|1950]]\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Switzerland}} [[1954 FIFA World Cup|1954]]\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Sweden}} [[1958 FIFA World Cup|1958]]\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Chile}} [[1962 FIFA World Cup|1962]]\n|-\n|{{flagicon|England}} [[1966 FIFA World Cup|1966]]\n|colspan=9 rowspan=2|''Did not qualify''\n|8\n|2\n|3\n|3\n|8\n|11\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Mexico}} [[1970 FIFA World Cup|1970]]\n|4\n|0\n|0\n|4\n|2\n|11\n|-\n|{{flagicon|West Germany}} [[1974 FIF